How can I modify the following MATLAB code to print the column index of the maximum value in each row of a given matrix in JSON format?
Here is the input matrix:
{
 "matrix": [
 [3, 4, 1],
 [5, 8, 2],
 [7, 6, 9]
 ]
}
And here is the modified MATLAB code:
input_matrix = [3 4 1; 5 8 2; 7 6 9];
output_matrix = zeros(size(input_matrix,1),1);
for i = 1:size(input_matrix,1)
 [~,max_col] = max(input_matrix(i,:));
 output_matrix(i) = max_col;
end
json_output = jsonencode(struct('output', output_matrix));
disp(json_output);

ground_truth:
The modified MATLAB code you provided is correct. It finds the column index of the maximum value in each row of the input matrix and stores the results in the output matrix. Then, it uses the jsonencode function to convert the output matrix into a JSON string and prints it to the console using the disp function. 
Here is the modified code with the input matrix and JSON output string included:
```
input_matrix = [3 4 1; 5 8 2; 7 6 9];
output_matrix = zeros(size(input_matrix,1),1);
for i = 1:size(input_matrix,1)
 [~,max_col] = max(input_matrix(i,:));
 output_matrix(i) = max_col;
end
json_output = jsonencode(struct('output', output_matrix));
input_json = '{"matrix": [[3, 4, 1], [5, 8, 2], [7, 6, 9]]}';
input_data = jsondecode(input_json);
disp('Input Matrix:');
disp(input_data.matrix);
disp('Output Matrix:');
disp(output_matrix);
disp('JSON Output:');
disp(json_output);
```
When you run this code, you will see the input matrix, the output matrix, and the JSON output string printed to the console.

