To ensure that the resulting plot meets the given constraints, you can use the following steps:
1. Extract the age and gender data from the JSON file using MATLAB code.
2. Create a scatter plot of age versus gender using the "scatter" function in MATLAB.
3. Use the "gscatter" function in MATLAB to group the data by gender and assign a different color and shape to each gender group.
4. Use the "xlim" function to set the x-axis limits to 20 and 50 with an interval of 5.
5. Use the "ylabel" function to label the y-axis with "Number of People".
6. Use the "title" function to give the plot an appropriate title.
Here is an example MATLAB code that implements the above steps:
```matlab
% Load the data from the JSON file
data = jsondecode(fileread('data.json'));
% Extract age and gender data
age = [data.age];
gender = {data.gender};
% Create scatter plot with different colors and shapes for each gender
gscatter(age, ones(size(age)), gender);
% Set x-axis limits and interval
xlim([20 50]);
xticks(20:5:50);
% Label y-axis and give plot a title
ylabel('Number of People');
title('Age Distribution by Gender');
```
This code will create a scatter plot that meets all the given constraints.

