Sure thing! To make the image responsive, you can use CSS media queries. Here's an example:
```python

 img {
 max-width: 100%;
 height: auto;
 }
 @media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
 img {
 max-width: 50%;
 }
 }

```
This sets the maximum width of the image to 100% of its container, and sets its height to adjust automatically to maintain the aspect ratio. The `@media` query makes it so that if the screen size is less than or equal to 600 pixels wide, the maximum width of the image is reduced to 50% of its container.

