Yes, you can use JavaScript to integrate with a wine API to provide recommendations for wine pairings with the dish. One example of a wine API you can use is the Wine.com API, which provides access to detailed information on over 50,000 different wines. Here's an example of how you can modify the previous code to include wine pairing recommendations:
1. First, sign up for a free account on the Wine.com API website and get an API key.
2. Add an additional input field to your HTML form for the user to enter their preferred type of wine (such as red or white).
```html

Broccoli:



Chicken:



Wine:



Submit

```
3. Modify the fetch() method to make a GET request to both the Spoonacular and Wine.com APIs, passing in the ingredients entered in the form and the preferred wine type. You can also use the Promise.all() method to wait for both requests to finish before processing the data.
```js
const form = document.querySelector('form');
const button = document.querySelector('button');
button.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
 event.preventDefault();
 const broccoli = document.getElementById('broccoli').value;
 const chicken = document.getElementById('chicken').value;
 const wine = document.getElementById('wine').value;
 const spoonacularUrl = `https://api.spoonacular.com/recipes/complexSearch?apiKey=YOUR_API_KEY&query=${broccoli}+${chicken}`;
 const winecomUrl = `https://api.wine.com/api/v1/pairing?food=${broccoli}%20${chicken}&wine=${wine}&apikey=YOUR_API_KEY`;
 Promise.all([
 fetch(spoonacularUrl).then(response => response.json()),
 fetch(winecomUrl).then(response => response.json())
 ]).then(data => {
 const spoonacularData = data[0];
 const winecomData = data[1];
 console.log(spoonacularData);
 console.log(winecomData);
 // Process the data and display it on the page
 }).catch(error => console.error(error));
});
```
4. Once you have the data from both APIs, you can process it to generate recipe and wine pairing suggestions. You can use a similar template literal approach to create HTML cards for each suggestion, including the recipe title, image, ingredients, instructions, and recommended wine pairings.
```js
const results = document.querySelector('.results');
spoonacularData.results.forEach(recipe => {
 const winePairings = winecomData.pairings.map(pairing => `- ${pairing}
`).join('');
 const card = `

 ![${recipe.title}](${recipe.image})
${recipe.title}
---------------
### Ingredients:

 ${recipe.extendedIngredients.map(ingredient => `* ${ingredient.original}
`).join('')}


### Instructions:

 ${recipe.analyzedInstructions[0].steps.map(step => `2. ${step.step}
`).join('')}


### Recommended Wine Pairings:

 ${winePairings}

 `;
 results.insertAdjacentHTML('beforeend', card);
});
```
