Certainly! Here is an example of an HTML code that uses logical reasoning to filter job openings based on Charlie's qualifications and preferred salary range:
```

Job Openings in New York City
Job Openings in New York City
=============================

Degree:

Select a degree
Computer Science
Other

Work Experience:

Select work experience
Customer Service
Other

Salary Range:

Select a salary range
$70,000 - $90,000 per year
Other

Filter


 const jobs = [
 {
 title: "Software Engineer",
 degree: "computer-science",
 experience: "other",
 salary: 100000
 },
 {
 title: "Customer Support Specialist",
 degree: "other",
 experience: "customer-service",
 salary: 75000
 },
 {
 title: "Web Developer",
 degree: "computer-science",
 experience: "other",
 salary: 80000
 },
 {
 title: "Technical Support Analyst",
 degree: "other",
 experience: "customer-service",
 salary: 85000
 },
 {
 title: "Database Administrator",
 degree: "computer-science",
 experience: "other",
 salary: 95000
 }
 ];
 const form = document.querySelector("form");
 const jobsDiv = document.querySelector("#jobs");
 form.addEventListener("submit", (event) => {
 event.preventDefault();
 const degree = form.elements["degree"].value;
 const experience = form.elements["experience"].value;
 const salary = form.elements["salary"].value;
 const filteredJobs = jobs.filter((job) => {
 if (degree && job.degree !== degree) {
 return false;
 }
 if (experience && job.experience !== experience) {
 return false;
 }
 if (salary && (job.salary < 70000 || job.salary > 90000)) {
 return false;
 }
 return true;
 });
 jobsDiv.innerHTML = "";
 if (filteredJobs.length === 0) {
 jobsDiv.innerHTML = "<p>No jobs found.</p>";
 } else {
 filteredJobs.forEach((job) => {
 const jobDiv = document.createElement("div");
 jobDiv.innerHTML = `<h2>${job.title}</h2><p>Salary: $${job.salary} per year</p>`;
 jobsDiv.appendChild(jobDiv);
 });
 }
 });

```
This code includes a form with three dropdown menus for degree, work experience, and salary range. When the user submits the form, the JavaScript code filters the job listings based on the selected options and displays the matching jobs in a div element. The code also includes an array of job objects with titles, degree requirements, work experience requirements, and salary information. The logical reasoning is implemented using the filter method to check if each job meets the selected criteria. Finally, the code includes a salary range check that only displays jobs that offer a salary range of $70,000 to $90,000 per year.

